
[1]student

   STUDENT, n. [L. See Study.]

   1. A person engaged in study; one who is devoted to learning, either in
   a seminary or in private; a scholar; as the students of an academy, of
   a college or university; a medical student; a law student.

   2. A man devoted to books; a bookish man; as a hard student; a close
   student.

   Keep a gamester from dice, and a good student from his books.

   3. One who studies or examines; as a student of natures works.
